[2]
Date: Sat 5 Jun 2010
Source: Japan Today [edited]
<http://www.japantoday.com/category/national/view/miyazaki-to-conduct-final-checks-on-5-stud-bulls>


Miyazaki to conduct final checks on 5 stud bulls
------------------------------------------------
The Miyazaki prefectural government said Friday [4 Jun 2010] it is
conducting final scientific checks on 5 top stud bulls of the
prefecture's cattle industry to see if they are infected with
foot-and-mouth disease [FMD].

The tests will be conducted at the Tokyo facility of the Tsukuba,
Ibaraki Prefecture-based National Institute of Animal Health, to
examine samples, taken from the bulls the same day, for the DNA of
the FMD virus or antibodies produced in reaction to the virus, it
said.

The samples including saliva were taken from the 5 bulls, which had
been transferred on 13 May 2010 to a refuge in the city of Saito from
a prefectural livestock center in Takanabe town.

The results of the DNA tests will be known on Saturday night [5 Jun
2010], while those of the antibody tests will be known on Sunday
night [6 Jun 2010].

